description: TSA agents across the country are looking to local food banks and other organizations for food as they continue working for a fifth week without pay amid the government shutdown.
title: Some TSA Agents Using Food Banks As Government Shutdown Grinds On #shorts

description: People are going bonkers for teddy bear glass cups at Starbucks. The 20-ounce holiday bottled called "Bearista Cold Cups," debuted Thursday and immediately sold out.
title: Starbucks 'Bearista' Becomes Instant Hit #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Nia Sioux was just 9 years old when she first appeared on "Dance Moms." Sioux is now 24 and recounting her seven seasons on the hit Lifetime TV show in her new memoir "Bottom of the Pyramid."
title: Nia Sioux Recalls 'Painful' Memories From 'Dance Moms' #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: These missing pets were found very far away from home. In October, a 3-year-old python mix who got out of her cage was found at an In-N-Out Burger 50 miles from her home. In 2017, Sarah Harris reunited with her pet skunk, Dottie, after it went missing while they were on a camping trip. In 2023, a cat named Butters was found after going missing from his San Diego home 12 years before. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: Missing Pets Found Very Far Away From Home

author: Inside Edition
description: A little boy made a promise to his mom that when he turned 16 and able to drive a car, he was going to take his mom on a date. The 4-year-old fidgeted with his shirt as his mom said she would not let him forget that moment. Fast forward 12 years later, and the boy, now a teen, stuck to his word. Emerson Longton took his mom, Megan, on a date to make pottery before a night out on the town. Inside Edition's Les Trent spoke with the mom and son.
title: Teen Keeps Special Promise To His Mom 12 Years Later
